,"date":"November 10, 2015","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn 'Abdul Barr reported: Sufyan al-Thawri, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cSurely, sacred knowledge is only studied to become mindful of Allah. Knowledge is only favored over other virtues because it makes one fearful of Allah.\u201d Source: Ja\u0304mi\u02bb Baya\u0304n al-\u02bbIlm li-Ibn 'Abd al-Barr 1159 \u0639\u0646 \u0627\u0628\u0646 \u0639\u0628\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":27256,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/03\/17\/ibn-masud-confusing-hadith\/","url_meta":{"origin":22218,"position":4},"title":"Ibn Mas\u2019ud on Caution: Not exposing confusing matters to common people","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 17, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"\u2018Ubaydullah reported: Abdullah ibn Mas\u2019ud, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cYou do not narrate to people what their minds cannot grasp but that it will be a trial for some of them.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 9 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Muslim Ibn Hajar said, \u201cIt is not\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":31342,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/05\/26\/ibn-abi-ghassan-remain-student\/","url_meta":{"origin":22218,"position":5},"title":"Ibn Abi Ghassan on Learning: You have knowledge if you remain a student","author":"Abu Ami